definition: something added to complete or embellish or make perfect, to make complete or perfect
details:
noun
- something added to complete or embellish or make perfect
= example: something added to complete or embellish or make perfect
= synonyms: accompaniment
- either of two parts that mutually complete each other
- a word or phrase used to complete a grammatical construction
- number needed to make up a whole force
= example: number needed to make up a whole force
= synonyms: full complement
- a complete number or quantity
= example: a complete number or quantity
- one of a series of enzymes in the blood serum that are part of the immune response
verb
- to make complete or perfect
= example: to make complete or perfect
